1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their deployment for tracking moving objects, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes algorithms for measuring road coverage metrics, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with monitoring moving objects, which is related to robotics. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new quality control metric for measuring the efficiency of a sensor network, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography and security, the deployment of wireless sensor networks for monitoring moving objects may have security implications, which could fall under the scope of cryptography and security.
